12/01/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha and his Socialist predecessor, Fatos Nano, met on Thursday (January 11th) and reportedly reached agreement regarding the upcoming local elections. At a press conference afterwards, Nano said all parties were constitutionally obligated to participate in the vote, now slated for February 18th. Local reports said Nano was seeking support from the ruling coalition for a possible presidential bid, in exchange for backing them with regard to the local elections. (Albanian News, Focus - 12/01/07) 
